ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Highlander Solar Energy Station 1, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
HIGHLANDER SOLAR ENERGY STATION 1, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Highlander Solar Energy Station 1, LLC ("Highlander Solar 1") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Highlander Solar 1 generating facility ("Highlander Solar 1 Facility").
The Highlander Solar 1 Facility is a solar generating facility located in Spotsylvania County, Virginia. The Highlander Solar 1 Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Highlander Solar 1's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Highlander Solar 1 Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Highlander Solar 1's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Highlander Solar 1 shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $2,166,431.83 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $180,535.99
